      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>American cartoonist and illustrator Vaughn Bodé (1941-1975) was a pioneer of the
            underground comics movement of the 1970s along with Spain Rodriguez, Robert Crumb and
            others.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The<emph render="bold"> Vaughn Bodé Collection</emph> consists of 8 items; 7 original
            drawings for the book <emph render="italic">A poet recognized; notes about Robert
               Frost's first trip to England and where he lived. With a letter by Lesley
               Frost</emph> by David Tatham and one signed printed poster.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
